formThreeModelMf.noteCertificate:
1.	For verifying the cost and period of the project, we have relied on the work order issued by Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation to the concerned contractor for the purpose of construction of the housing scheme and the period mentioned in the work order.

2.	For the purpose of verifying the number of units in the project, we have relied on the Commencement letter issued by Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation.

3.	The figures placed in the owned funds, customer receipts and others (if any) in the sheet of Means of Finance have been put up based on the information provided by the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation vide its mail dated 26-11-2024.

4.	For the purpose of verifying the unit cost of the project, we have relied on circular no. AHM/102015/453/TH-1 dated 15-12-2016 issued by Urban Development & Urban Housing Department of Government of Gujarat.

5.	For the purpose of incurred & paid expense as mentioned in MOF of the project, we have considered the value of work completed as mentioned in the latest audited running account bill of the project.

formThreeIdData.notesToCertificate:
1. The amount of construction cost has been considered on the basis of the information provided by the competent authorities of the Corporation.
2. Total number of units to be constructed has been assumed to be built up evenly.
3. Land valuation method has been selected as "ASR value" based on the information provided by Housing Project Department vide it's mail dated 13-06-2024 that "Jantri rates" have been adopted for land valuation.
4. As per Housing Cell department's mail dated 04-06-2024, forms for the allotment of houses for EWS-52 have not yet been invited.
5. As informed by the Housing Project vide its mail dated 21-06-2024, the development cost of 27 shops is Rs.19666717.20/- and as was informed to us on 24-06-2024, Estate Department will handle the auction process of these
27 shops of EWS-52 after the project has been completed and shops have been constructed. Thus, the sales price of these 27 shops cannot be determined at this stage when the construction is under progress. Hence,
development cost of these 27 shops i.e. Rs.19666717.20/- has been considered as their total sales price at this stage and the same has been proportionately distributed amongst each of the 27 shops based on the respective carpet area as shown in the project drawing provided by the Housing Project.
6. This Form-3 for RERA registration is being filed as a response the queries of RERA department.
